# Material UI + styling

This app uses **MUI v9** (`@mui/material`) with Emotion. A theme already exists at
`src/theme.js` and is applied via `<ThemeProvider>` in `AppShell.jsx`.

## API docs (reference these before hand-rolling a component)

- Components overview: https://mui.com/material-ui/all-components/
- Component API index: https://mui.com/material-ui/api/
- `sx` prop: https://mui.com/system/getting-started/the-sx-prop/
- Theming: https://mui.com/material-ui/customization/theming/
- Default theme (token names): https://mui.com/material-ui/customization/default-theme/
- Migration / v9 notes: https://mui.com/material-ui/migration/
- Commonly needed here: [TextField](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-text-field/),
  [Select](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-select/), [Button](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-button/),
  [Table](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-table/), [Chip](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-chip/),
  [Dialog](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-dialog/), [Tabs](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-tabs/),
  [Card/Paper](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-card/), [Stack](https://mui.com/material-ui/react-stack/).

## Rules

1. **Prefer MUI components** over hand-rolled `<select>`/`<input>`/`<table>`/`<button>` +
   inline styles. Reach for `TextField`, `Select`, `Button`, `Chip`, `Table`, `Dialog`, `Stack`.
2. **Never hardcode hex colors.** Use theme tokens via `sx`:
   `sx={{ color: 'primary.main', bgcolor: 'background.paper' }}`. If a color/spacing isn't in
   `src/theme.js`, add it there (palette / spacing / custom `theme.bco.*`) instead of inlining it.
3. **Style with `sx`, not `style={{}}`.** `sx` gets theme access, media-query shorthands, and
   pseudo-selectors. Reserve inline `style` for truly one-off dynamic values.
4. **Don't duplicate a component.** Search for an existing shared component (e.g. a single
   `FormSelect`) before writing a new near-identical one.

```jsx
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded palette, hand-rolled control
<select style={{ border: "1px solid #DCD6C4", borderRadius: 8, color: "#2C2A22" }}>…</select>

// ✅ GOOD — MUI + theme tokens
<Select size="small" value={value} onChange={(e) => onChange(e.target.value)}>
  {options.map((o) => <MenuItem key={o.value} value={o.value}>{o.label}</MenuItem>)}
</Select>
```
